This paper is about declarative machine learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper discusses the different types of declarative ML and provides a taxonomy for them. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases), as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of declarative machine learning. Additionally, the paper discusses the development of declarative ML systems, which could also be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
